        <script src="../scripts/main.js"></script>
        <style>
            .page-container {
                display: flex;
                flex-direction: column;
                gap: 40px;
                padding-bottom: 60px;
            }

            section {
                border-radius: 30px;
                overflow: hidden;
                margin: 0 30px;
                position: relative;
            }

            h2 {
                font-family: "grenadine-mvb", sans-serif;
                font-size: 2.5rem;
                margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
                line-height: 1.2;
            }

            p {
                font-size: 1.15rem;
                line-height: 1.8;
                margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
                color: var(--color-text);
            }

            /* 1. Philosophy Section */
            .philosophy-section {
                background: var(--color-white);
                padding: 6rem 4rem;
                text-align: center;
                background-image: radial-gradient(var(--color-3) 1px, transparent 1px);
                background-size: 40px 40px;
                background-color: #fff;
            }

            .philosophy-content {
                max-width: 800px;
                margin: 0 auto;
                background: white;
                padding: 3rem;
                border-radius: 20px;
                box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
                border: 2px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
            }

            /* 2. Patterns Section */
            .patterns-section {
                background: var(--color-card-bg);
                padding: 5rem 4rem;
            }

            .patterns-grid {
                display: grid;
                grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
                gap: 4rem;
                margin-top: 3rem;
            }

            .pattern-card {
                background: var(--color-white);
                border-radius: 20px;
                padding: 2.5rem;
                border: 3px solid transparent;
                transition: transform 0.3s;
            }

            .pattern-card:hover {
                transform: translateY(-5px);
            }

            .pattern-card.students {
                border-color: var(--color-1);
            }

            .pattern-card.teachers {
                border-color: var(--color-2);
            }

            .pattern-list {
                list-style: none;
                margin-top: 1.5rem;
            }

            .pattern-list li {
                position: relative;
                padding-left: 2rem;
                margin-bottom: 1rem;
                font-size: 1.1rem;
            }

            .pattern-card.students .pattern-list li::before {
                content: '‚óè';
                color: var(--color-1);
                position: absolute;
                left: 0;
            }

            .pattern-card.teachers .pattern-list li::before {
                content: '‚óè';
                color: var(--color-2);
                position: absolute;
                left: 0;
            }

            /* 3. Signals Section */
            .signals-section {
                background: var(--color-text);
                color: var(--color-white);
                padding: 6rem 4rem;
                display: grid;
                grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
                gap: 4rem;
                align-items: center;
            }

            .signals-section h2, .signals-section p {
                color: var(--color-white);
            }

            .signal-visual {
                background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
                border-radius: 20px;
                padding: 3rem;
                text-align: center;
                border: 2px dashed rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
            }

            .dinner-icon {
                font-size: 4rem;
                margin-bottom: 1rem;
                display: block;
            }

            /* 4. Voices Section */
            .voices-section {
                background: var(--color-4); /* Yellow */
                padding: 5rem 4rem;
            }

            .voices-grid {
                display: grid;
                grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
                gap: 2rem;
                margin-top: 3rem;
            }

            .voice-card {
                background: var(--color-white);
                padding: 2rem;
                border-radius: 16px;
                position: relative;
                box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            }
            
            .voice-card::before {
                content: '"';
                font-family: serif;
                font-size: 4rem;
                color: rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
                position: absolute;
                top: 10px;
                left: 20px;
                line-height: 1;
            }

            .voice-text {
                font-style: italic;
                font-size: 1.1rem;
                margin-bottom: 1rem;
                position: relative;
                z-index: 1;
            }

            .voice-author {
                font-weight: bold;
                text-align: right;
                font-size: 0.9rem;
                color: var(--color-text);
                opacity: 0.7;
                text-transform: uppercase;
                letter-spacing: 1px;
            }

            /* 5. Conclusion Section */
            .conclusion-section {
                text-align: center;
                padding: 5rem 2rem;
            }

            .conclusion-list {
                display: inline-flex;
                flex-direction: column;
                align-items: flex-start;
                gap: 1rem;
                margin: 2rem auto;
                text-align: left;
            }

            .check-item {
                font-size: 1.25rem;
                font-weight: 500;
                display: flex;
                align-items: center;
                gap: 1rem;
            }
            
            .check-item span {
                color: var(--color-3);
                font-weight: bold;
                font-size: 1.5rem;
            }

            /* Responsive */
            @media (max-width: 1024px) {
                .patterns-grid, .signals-section {
                    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
                }
            }

            @media (max-width: 600px) {
                section {
                    margin: 0;
                    border-radius: 0;
                    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
                }
                .philosophy-content {
                    padding: 1.5rem;
                }
            }
        </style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<div id="smooth-wrapper">
			<div id="smooth-content">
				<Navbar />
				
                <main class="page-container">
                    
                    <div style="text-align: center; padding: 2rem 1rem 0;">
                        <h1 class="hero-title" style="opacity: 1; transform: none; animation: none; font-size: 3.5rem; font-family: 'grenadine-mvb', sans-serif;">Impact & <span style="color: var(--color-2);">Voices</span></h1>
                    </div>

                    <!-- 1. Philosophy -->
                    <section class="philosophy-section">
                        <div class="philosophy-content">
                            <h2>How We Think About Impact</h2>
                            <p>At Games For Ed, we‚Äôre cautious about how we talk about impact.</p>
                            <p>We don‚Äôt look for loud transformations or instant results. We pay attention to smaller signals that tell us whether learning is landing.</p>
                            <p>Sometimes those signals show up in the classroom. Sometimes they show up later, at home, during dinner table conversations. <strong>Both matter.</strong></p>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <!-- 2. Patterns -->
                    <section class="patterns-section">
                        <div style="text-align: center; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
                            <h2>What We‚Äôre Seeing So Far</h2>
                            <p>Across our sessions and early pilots, a few patterns keep repeating.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="patterns-grid">
                            <div class="pattern-card students">
                                <h3 style="color: var(--color-1); font-family: 'grenadine-mvb', sans-serif; font-size: 1.5rem;">Students Tend To:</h3>
                                <ul class="pattern-list">
                                    <li>Stay engaged for longer than expected</li>
                                    <li>Explain their thinking more clearly during play</li>
                                    <li>Reference earlier choices during reflection</li>
                                    <li>Remember details days after the session</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                            <div class="pattern-card teachers">
                                <h3 style="color: var(--color-2); font-family: 'grenadine-mvb', sans-serif; font-size: 1.5rem;">Teachers Often Notice:</h3>
                                <ul class="pattern-list">
                                    <li>Quieter students participate more actively</li>
                                    <li>Collaboration feels more balanced</li>
                                    <li>Assessment becomes more visible through discussion</li>
                                    <li>Conversations continue beyond the session</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <!-- 3. Signals -->
                    <section class="signals-section">
                        <div>
                            <h2>Why These Signals Matter to Us</h2>
                            <p>Learning doesn‚Äôt always announce itself. It shows up when students:</p>
                            <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
                                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">‚Ä¢ Can retell an experience in their own words</li>
                                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">‚Ä¢ Connect ideas across contexts</li>
                                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">‚Ä¢ Revisit decisions after time has passed</li>
                                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">‚Ä¢ Feel confident enough to explain, not just answer</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="signal-visual">
                            <span class="dinner-icon">üçΩÔ∏è</span>
                            <h3 style="font-family: 'grenadine-mvb', sans-serif; font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--color-white);">The Dinner Table Test</h3>
                            <p style="font-size: 1rem; opacity: 0.9;">"Dinner table conversations are one of many places where this becomes visible. Not because they are planned, but because they are unprompted. For us, that matters."</p>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <!-- 4. Voices -->
                    <section class="voices-section">
                        <h2 style="text-align: center;">Voices from the Classroom</h2>
                        <div class="voices-grid">
                            <!-- Student Voices -->
                            <div class="voice-card">
                                <p class="voice-text">I liked that we had to decide together. I told my parents what our group argued about.</p>
                                <div class="voice-author">- Student</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="voice-card">
                                <p class="voice-text">At first it was confusing, but later it made sense when I explained it at home.</p>
                                <div class="voice-author">- Student</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="voice-card">
                                <p class="voice-text">I remembered the rules even after a few days.</p>
                                <div class="voice-author">- Student</div>
                            </div>
                             <div class="voice-card">
                                <p class="voice-text">I don‚Äôt usually talk in class, but in the game I had to.</p>
                                <div class="voice-author">- Student</div>
                            </div>

                            <!-- Teacher Voices -->
                            <div class="voice-card" style="background: var(--color-secondary-bg); border: 2px solid var(--color-2);">
                                <p class="voice-text">Students who don‚Äôt usually speak were much more involved.</p>
                                <div class="voice-author" style="color: var(--color-2);">- Teacher</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="voice-card" style="background: var(--color-secondary-bg); border: 2px solid var(--color-2);">
                                <p class="voice-text">I could see their thinking clearly while they were playing.</p>
                                <div class="voice-author" style="color: var(--color-2);">- Teacher</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="voice-card" style="background: var(--color-secondary-bg); border: 2px solid var(--color-2);">
                                <p class="voice-text">Some parents mentioned their children talking about the activity at home.</p>
                                <div class="voice-author" style="color: var(--color-2);">- Teacher</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <!-- 5. Conclusion -->
                    <section class="conclusion-section">
                        <h2>What This Means for Schools</h2>
                        <p>We‚Äôre still building and learning, and we‚Äôre transparent about that.<br>But these patterns give us confidence that our approach supports:</p>
                        
                        <div class="conclusion-list">
                            <div class="check-item"><span>‚úì</span> Deeper engagement</div>
                            <div class="check-item"><span>‚úì</span> Clearer thinking</div>
                            <div class="check-item"><span>‚úì</span> Stronger student voice</div>
                            <div class="check-item"><span>‚úì</span> Learning that doesn‚Äôt end when the class does</div>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
                             <a href="/#contact" class="cta-button">See It In Action</a>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                </main>

					<footer class="footer">
						<div class="footer-content">
							<div class="footer-logo">
								<img src="/gamesfored.avif" alt="Games for Learning" />
							</div>
							<div class="footer-copyright">
								<p>&copy; 2025 GamesForEd. All rights reserved.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</footer>
			</div>
		</div>
	</body>
</html>